cveDescription: org.eclipse.jetty_jetty-servlet package versions before 9.4.44 are vulnerable to DoS (Denial of Service). Logback-access calls Request.getParameterNames() for request logging. That will force a request body read (if it hasn\\'t been read before) per the servlet. This will now consume resources to read the request body content\, which could easily be malicious (in size? in keys? etc)\, even though the application intentionally didn\\'t read the request body.
